<div id="review_3951361742" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3951361742" />
    <a title="Nehal " class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/122561225-nehal"><img alt="Nehal " src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1627797364p2/122561225.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3951361742?book_show_action=true">Apr 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Nehal " class="user" itemprop="url" name="Nehal " href="/user/show/122561225-nehal">Nehal </a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3951361742" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13288291716383758540">○The story starts off with Biniya taking her cows back home and it ends the same way meaning her umbrella does change her life but not entirely she still will have to do her mundane chores. So the umbrella did give her a boost of fame but does not have a permanent impact on her life.<br/><br/><br/>○While trading, she gave away a piece of her luck too as the next scene describes people envying her.<br/><br/><br/>○Usually, new things are welcomed with a spark of joy in the eyes whereas here the villagers had nothing but envy i</span>
  <span id="freeText13288291716383758540" style="display:none">○The story starts off with Biniya taking her cows back home and it ends the same way meaning her umbrella does change her life but not entirely she still will have to do her mundane chores. So the umbrella did give her a boost of fame but does not have a permanent impact on her life.<br /><br /><br />○While trading, she gave away a piece of her luck too as the next scene describes people envying her.<br /><br /><br />○Usually, new things are welcomed with a spark of joy in the eyes whereas here the villagers had nothing but envy in theirs. But as the story progresses we see the same villagers building up trust in Biniya and her generosity when she decides to share her umbrella. Here, I think sharing an umbrella is equivalent to sharing love.<br /><br /><br />○Biniya did not give a second thought while selling her leopard claw in exchange for a blue umbrella, showing that something new holds more value than the one which is old.<br /><br /><br />○<b>
  <i>Binya was probably ten. She may have been nine or even eleven, she couldn’t be sure because no one in the village kept birthdays; but her mother told her she’d been born during a winter when the snow had come up to the windows, and that was just over ten years ago, wasn’t it?</i>
</b><br /><br /><br />I love how Ruskin bond manages to add a tidbit of how global warming has impacted this village.<br /><br /><br /><b>
  <i>○“But how torn and dirty her clothes are!” it did not seem to bother them that Binya could hear and understand everything they said about her.<br /><br />“Oh, I want one too!” said the woman, who was obviously his wife.<br />“You can’t get them in shops.”<br />“Buy hers, then. Give her two or three rupees, she’s sure to need the money.”</i>
</b><br /><br />The couple knew the value the pendant held yet they settled on offering her a buck or two. The state of her clothes and her age made them do so. I love how natural yet thought-provoking this scene is!<br /><br /><b>
  <i>○"Unlike the adults, the children didn’t have to pretend."</i>
</b><br />Again, a beautiful commentary on how growing up leads to the loss of innocence. <br /><br />I thoroughly enjoyed this book it was short yet filled with great mountain vibes. The cherry on top for me was the writing style it was simple yet beautiful.<br /><br /><s>I need time to ponder upon it.</s><br />_______________________________________<br />I would like to thank <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/show/128191325-bhavya" rel="nofollow noopener">Bhavya</a> for giving me a little push into this magnificent world Ruskin bond has created.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13288291716383758540" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


