<span id="freeTextContainer2936798108680892599">The blue Umbrella by Ruskin Bond is a short read.<br/><br/>The story whirls around Binya a 9 year old girl who lives in a village. She come across a blue umbrella which she wants to own it. <br/>Will she have that umbrella? Is someone there who also wants to own it? What happens next lies the suspense of the story.<br/><br/>Ruskin Bond is an awesome author. I always admired his work, this is another master piece. The pacing of the story is precicse and intact. Language is kept simple and easy to read. I would recommend </span>
  <span id="freeText2936798108680892599" style="display:none">The blue Umbrella by Ruskin Bond is a short read.<br /><br />The story whirls around Binya a 9 year old girl who lives in a village. She come across a blue umbrella which she wants to own it. <br />Will she have that umbrella? Is someone there who also wants to own it? What happens next lies the suspense of the story.<br /><br />Ruskin Bond is an awesome author. I always admired his work, this is another master piece. The pacing of the story is precicse and intact. Language is kept simple and easy to read. I would recommend this book to young readers who loves reading.</span>
